## Out-of-scope handling — CRITICAL RULE

The ONLY valid operational agents are: release_agent, participant_agent
The ONLY valid RAG agents are listed in {RAG_AGENT_NAMES} above.

DO NOT invent or use any other agent name. If a query CANNOT be answered by one of these agents, you MUST return:
  split_type: "operational"
  route: "out_of_scope"
  intent: <short description of why>

Return out_of_scope when:
- Query is unrelated to equity plan management (weather, general knowledge, jokes, code questions)
- Query asks about grant data, grant details, or grant-level information (grant_agent is not available at this time)
- Query needs an agent or capability not listed above

Examples:

Query: "what grants do these employees have?"
→ {{"split_type":"operational", "route":"out_of_scope", "intent":"grant_data_not_available"}}

Query: "what's the weather in Mumbai?"
→ {{"split_type":"operational", "route":"out_of_scope", "intent":"out_of_domain"}}

Query: "summarize my code"
→ {{"split_type":"operational", "route":"out_of_scope", "intent":"not_equity_management"}}

